- **Disease Type**: The Lyme disease market can be segmented based on different disease types including Lyme Carditis, Lyme Arthritis, Neurologic Lyme Disease, Borrelial Lymphocytosis, and Post-treatment Lyme Disease Syndrome, each requiring specific treatment approaches.
- **Stages Type**: The stages of Lyme disease include Localized Early Stage, Disseminated Stage, and Late Stage, which determine the severity of the infection and aid in identifying the appropriate treatment strategy.
- **Treatment Type**: Treatment options for Lyme disease vary and may include medication like antibiotics and anti-inflammatory drugs, as well as physical interventions such as tick removal to prevent further transmission.
- **Diagnosis Type**: Diagnosis of Lyme disease involves various tests such as Blood Test, Serological Test, Urine Antigen Tests, Lymphocytic Transformation Test, Immuno fluorescent Staining, Nucleic acid Test, and Enzyme-linked Immunosorbent Assay (ELISA) Test, which help in confirming the presence of the Borrelia burgdorferi bacterium in the body.
- **Drug Type**: Commonly prescribed drugs for Lyme disease treatment include Doxycycline, Cefuroxime axetil, Amoxicillin, Ceftriaxone, and others, each targeting different aspects of the infection to speed up recovery.
